    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n'exrc' `.nvim.lua` scripts don't have a way to [find their own location](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/3910#issuecomment-2980236531).\n\n> `debug.getinfo(1, 'S').source:sub(2)` could not be used since `.source` value it returns from inside of `.nvim.lua` is just `\"<nvim>\"`, there's no file path.\n\nThis is rather relevant for 'exrc' scripts since they are by definition project-local / workspace-local, and they need to know the project they are in.\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither we need to source 'exrc' scripts in a way that allows `debug.getinfo(...).source` to work, or we need some other mechanism that provides a way for scripts to reliably know their location:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32116",
